    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Will Smith** (73.95) and **Tyler Freeman** (71.80) anchor the offense as our highest-rated plays. **Will Smith** benefits from a stellar combination of a hitter-friendly park and a favorable matchup against Lorenzen, while **Tyler Freeman** receives a significant efficiency boost (+19% SP Skill) facing a vulnerable starter in Sasaki. Meanwhile, **Jonathan Aranda** (67.96) is a high-upside play at 1B; his value is bolstered by a potent wind-out condition and a strong platoon advantage against Keller, making him a prime candidate for power production. We also see solid output from **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (65.51) and **Bryson Stott** (64.41), both of whom are clear starts based on their dynamic platoon splits and high-leverage spots in the batting order.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involves **Matt Chapman** (52.85), who narrowly missed the starting cut. While his projected efficiency remains solid, he was edged out by our starting MI/UTIL options who benefited from more favorable park factors and specific platoon matchups. Elsewhere, **Gleyber Torres** (52.28) and **Wenceel Perez** (47.28) carry elevated risk today as they navigate a challenging encounter with Crochet; despite the park boost, the SP skill of the opposing pitcher drags their ceilings down. We are similarly cautious with **Jeremiah Jackson** (45.49) and **Jung Hoo Lee** (45.51), who remain active but must be monitored closely as they fall toward our floor of 40.0. **Drew Gilbert** has been benched outright, as his sub-40 score signals a need to preserve game caps in a low-efficiency environment. As always, keep a sharp eye on the late-afternoon lineups, as any shuffling for **Yainer Diaz** or **Taylor Ward** could shift these daily efficiency scores rapidly.",
